From 6139a300499ee1926b94bf76f8a04f23e7fb3b12 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramesh Mandal <ramesh@6epixels.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 14:29:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(realtime): Socket.IO server + live cross-browser
 messaging

Backend (apps/backend):
- minimal Socket.IO relay: hello/roster (presence), dm routing by
  username, typing relay; in-memory, protocol designed to survive the
  NestJS+Postgres upgrade
- tsx dev/start scripts, wired into turbo

Extension:
- lib/realtime.ts transport (connect, roster/dm/typing handlers, send);
  stores import it, it imports no stores
- chat.store: live flag, applyRoster (live contacts u-<username>,
  departed users flip offline, demo contacts preserved), receiveDm
  (ensures contact+conversation, unread when not viewing), receiveTyping
  (3s auto-clear); outgoing messages route via deliver(): socket for
  live contacts, canned replies for demo
- WorkspaceScreen connects on mount with profile identity; graceful
  fallback to demo mode when server unreachable
- WorkspaceHeader: Live/Demo status pill + presence dot
- ChatView: relays typing to live contacts (1.5s throttle)
- Sign out disconnects the socket

Verified: two-client integration test - roster, typing relay, text DM,
link DM (share-tab shape), presence on disconnect. 5/5 checks pass.
